id: pm-github-77wj
title: export --apply exits 0 even when every item fails to write
description: "The export --apply handler calls applyExportPlan() and then returns { applied:true, ... } and exits 0 regardless of outcome. Per-item-continue isolation is intentional, but when a non-empty plan results in zero successes and at least one failure (created===0 && updated===0 && failed>0) the command still exited 0. A CI/script step would see success when nothing was written to GitHub."
type: Issue
status: in_progress
priority: 2
tags: []
created_at: "2026-06-13T07:19:57.156Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-13T07:19:57.156Z"
author: codex
acceptance_criteria: "Non-empty all-fail batch throws CommandError(GENERIC_FAILURE=1) after the per-item errors/summary are emitted; partial success (>=1 created/updated) still exits 0; empty plan still exits 0; unit tests cover all-fail/partial/empty/full via applyOutcomeError; release:check green."
body: ""
